  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Central nervous system (CNS) relapses of aggressive lymphomas are a rare but devastating
      complication. There is no therapy standard, conventional approaches are palliative. This
      study investigates an intensive chemotherapy with CNS penetrating drugs followed by high-dose
      chemotherapy and autologous stem cell transplantation as a potentially curative approach.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
